The paper deals with the characterization and search algorithm for elementary trapping sets (ETSs) in low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as simulation results (cs.SI) and network information theory (cs.NI).
